Module ehubicka.inventory
Package Controller

Class ModifyPart

java.lang.Object
Controller.ModifyPart
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.fxml.Initializable
public class ModifyPart extends Object implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
This class will utilize the ModifyPart form which modifies an already existing instance of a part to be updated back into the parts inventory

    • sendPart

      public void sendPart(Part part)
      This method transfers over part data from the MainScreen to the ModifyPart screen. The textfields will autopopulate with data from the selected part. It is used in the toModifyPartScreen method in the MainScreen controller.
      Parameters:
      part - is the instance of a part selected from the MainScreen controller tableview

    • modifyPart

      public void modifyPart(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      Compile data input from the form to modify an existing part. This part will be updated and added back into the part Inventory. User is redirected back to the MainScreen view. Different alerts are displayed for the form not being filled out correctly.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - triggered when the save button is selected
      Throws:
      IOException - when an IO error occurs
